&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Here, the transformation will be &amp;quot;E&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;PQFEPPS&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Thus, according to the final arrangement, &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;E&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;QFEPP&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; there are two&amp;nbsp;alphabets i.e&amp;nbsp;Q&amp;nbsp;and R&amp;nbsp;between the alphabet which is 2&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;nd&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;from the left&amp;nbsp; i.e &amp;#39;P&amp;#39; and 1&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;st&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;from the right &amp;#39;S&amp;#39; &lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;according to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;English alphabetical series&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color:  (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Two&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The logic follows here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Two opposite faces are never together or adjacent to each other.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;There is a pattern in which unfolded dice occur opposite to each other.&lt;/p&gt;

